Provides Direction & Navigation 

GeoCoding
  address → (lat, lon)

GeoHash
  (lat, lon) → string
  Finds near by using prefix matching

Tiles
  Break world into small fixed regions
  Tile Creation
    GeoHash/S2/QuadTree

  Map
    Stored in S3 and cached at CDN
    Resolution 
      1-21
    Format
      Raster(PNG)
      Vector
        Rendered on client using WebGL

  Route
    Roads : Edge
    Intersection : Node
    Stored in S3 and cached aggressively at Service

Graph
  Nodes Intersection
  Edges Roads
  Road Hierarchy

    Level 1 → Local roads
    Level 2 → Arterial roads
    Level 3 → Highways

    Reduces search space drastically


Navigation
  1) Input Source, Destination
  2) GeoCoding
  3) GeoHashing
  4) Tile Loading
  5) Find Top-K paths
  6) ETA for each using traffic live and historic data, and using ML
  7) Rank each and return 

Location 
  1) Client → Sends Location every few seconds
  2) Storage
      Casandra
      (userId, timestamp) → (lat, lon)
  3) Kafka for down-streaming service


Tiles : Reduce memory + CPU, Caching,
Hierarchy : Avoid scanning all roads, Jump to highways first
Cassandra : Heavy writes (location updates), availablity > consistency




    
  
